        <title>Cool Math Art</title>
        <link>https://thedarklynx.com/p/cool-math-art/</link>
        <pubDate>Sat, 31 Aug 2024 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
        
        <guid>https://thedarklynx.com/p/cool-math-art/</guid>
        <description>&lt;p&gt;Desmos is a great math tool, but people also make some insane math art on it.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Of course I&amp;rsquo;ve dabbled in it too, here is a picture of a duck I made in Desmos:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&#34;https://thedarklynx.com/p/cool-math-art/MohawkDuck.png&#34;
	width=&#34;536&#34;
	height=&#34;397&#34;
	srcset=&#34;https://thedarklynx.com/p/cool-math-art/MohawkDuck_hu1c3f6ea36607ee079875b6723a504881_38013_480x0_resize_box_3.png 480w, https://thedarklynx.com/p/cool-math-art/MohawkDuck_hu1c3f6ea36607ee079875b6723a504881_38013_1024x0_resize_box_3.png 1024w&#34;
	loading=&#34;lazy&#34;
	
		alt=&#34;Mohawk Duck!!&#34;
	
	
		class=&#34;gallery-image&#34; 
		data-flex-grow=&#34;135&#34;
		data-flex-basis=&#34;324px&#34;
	
&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Think that&amp;rsquo;s impressive? It&amp;rsquo;s time for myself to be humbled. Here is a gallery of some of my favorite art pieces for the Desmos Art Competition 2023. You can find more on the &lt;a class=&#34;link&#34; href=&#34;https://www.desmos.com/art&#34;  target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;
    &gt;official site.&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Here is a really cool picture of the Hudson River. &lt;a class=&#34;link&#34; href=&#34;https://www.desmos.com/calculator/nkwvtfuv99&#34;  target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;
    &gt;This one is created by Richard He&lt;/a&gt;:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&#34;https://thedarklynx.com/p/cool-math-art/SunsetHudsonRichardHe.png&#34;
	width=&#34;758&#34;
	height=&#34;575&#34;
	srcset=&#34;https://thedarklynx.com/p/cool-math-art/SunsetHudsonRichardHe_hubf7e265ae734873dac0802f10e68bde1_203507_480x0_resize_box_3.png 480w, https://thedarklynx.com/p/cool-math-art/SunsetHudsonRichardHe_hubf7e265ae734873dac0802f10e68bde1_203507_1024x0_resize_box_3.png 1024w&#34;
	loading=&#34;lazy&#34;
	
		alt=&#34;&amp;ldquo;Sunset on the Hudson&amp;rdquo; by Richard He&#34;
	
	
		class=&#34;gallery-image&#34; 
		data-flex-grow=&#34;131&#34;
		data-flex-basis=&#34;316px&#34;
	
&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This one is actually a piano playing some music! You can do this through the &amp;quot;play graph&amp;quot; feature desmos offers. &lt;a class=&#34;link&#34; href=&#34;https://www.desmos.com/calculator/yvchjdew6g&#34;  target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;
    &gt;This piece is by Nick Ertman&lt;/a&gt;:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&#34;https://thedarklynx.com/p/cool-math-art/TempestNickErtman.png&#34;
	width=&#34;1182&#34;
	height=&#34;808&#34;
	srcset=&#34;https://thedarklynx.com/p/cool-math-art/TempestNickErtman_hu5450a74a80770ee246ad175db7f3d484_50419_480x0_resize_box_3.png 480w, https://thedarklynx.com/p/cool-math-art/TempestNickErtman_hu5450a74a80770ee246ad175db7f3d484_50419_1024x0_resize_box_3.png 1024w&#34;
	loading=&#34;lazy&#34;
	
		alt=&#34;&amp;ldquo;Playing the Tempest&amp;rdquo; by Nick Ertman&#34;
	
	
		class=&#34;gallery-image&#34; 
		data-flex-grow=&#34;146&#34;
		data-flex-basis=&#34;351px&#34;
	
&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This one is a really, really impressive drawing (or calculation) of a nighttime diner. &lt;a class=&#34;link&#34; href=&#34;https://www.desmos.com/calculator/1cwbqzjqjm&#34;  target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;
    &gt;This is created by Judy Luo&lt;/a&gt;:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&#34;https://thedarklynx.com/p/cool-math-art/NighthawksJudyLuo.png&#34;
	width=&#34;994&#34;
	height=&#34;557&#34;
	srcset=&#34;https://thedarklynx.com/p/cool-math-art/NighthawksJudyLuo_hue4046d5f3db1fdad994946a13324a97e_137517_480x0_resize_box_3.png 480w, https://thedarklynx.com/p/cool-math-art/NighthawksJudyLuo_hue4046d5f3db1fdad994946a13324a97e_137517_1024x0_resize_box_3.png 1024w&#34;
	loading=&#34;lazy&#34;
	
		alt=&#34;&amp;ldquo;Nighthawks&amp;rdquo; by Judy Luo&#34;
	
	
		class=&#34;gallery-image&#34; 
		data-flex-grow=&#34;178&#34;
		data-flex-basis=&#34;428px&#34;
	
&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;And last for this post, this one is a 3D model of a piano that also plays some music: Clair de Lune by Claude DeBussy. &lt;a class=&#34;link&#34; href=&#34;https://www.desmos.com/3d/4fe020e052&#34;  target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;
    &gt;This was made by Audrey Chiang&lt;/a&gt;:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&#34;https://thedarklynx.com/p/cool-math-art/ClaireDeLuneAudreyChiang.png&#34;
	width=&#34;918&#34;
	height=&#34;783&#34;
	srcset=&#34;https://thedarklynx.com/p/cool-math-art/ClaireDeLuneAudreyChiang_hu2d6c570bcee2271366816d98aa6e03f4_97597_480x0_resize_box_3.png 480w, https://thedarklynx.com/p/cool-math-art/ClaireDeLuneAudreyChiang_hu2d6c570bcee2271366816d98aa6e03f4_97597_1024x0_resize_box_3.png 1024w&#34;
	loading=&#34;lazy&#34;
	
		alt=&#34;&amp;ldquo;Clair de Lune&amp;rdquo; by Audrey Chiang&#34;
	
	
		class=&#34;gallery-image&#34; 
		data-flex-grow=&#34;117&#34;
		data-flex-basis=&#34;281px&#34;
	
&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Once again this was all Desmos! I couldn&amp;rsquo;t even do this with an actual paintbrush! Really amazing how these creative people managed to do it with mathematical equations. Once again, this stuff is really really cool!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Go check them out in the gallery! I&amp;rsquo;ll see you in another post!&lt;/p&gt;
